Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the noodles.

Trim and halve the @green beans{80%grams}. Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain the @king prawns{150%grams}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Once boiling, add the @egg noodle nests{2} and green beans to the pan of boiling water. Cook until
tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{80%grams} and @coleslaw mix{120%grams} and season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Fry, stirring occasionally, until starting to brown ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the prawns, adding a drizzle of more @oil{} if needed.

Fry until the prawns are cooked and the veg is starting to soften, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

While everything cooks, in a #measuring jug{}, combine the @ketjap manis{50%grams},
@rice vinegar{30%milliliter} and @cornflour{10%grams}. Mix well until smooth.

Once smooth, add the @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%milliliter}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix until well combined.

> See pantry for sugar and water amounts - 1 tsp sugar and 100ml water for the sauce.

Once your prawns and veg are cooked, add the garlic and fry, ~{1%minute} more.

Lower the heat to medium, then add sticky sauce. Stir to combine and simmer until the sauce
has reduced slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the heat, then taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of
@water{} if you feel it needs it.

Add the cooked noodles and beans to the prawn stir-fry and toss to coat well in the sauce.

Share the sticky prawn noodles between your bowls. Sprinkle over the spring onion to finish.

Enjoy!